# AI Game Master - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
AI-driven Game Master orchestration engine for tabletop RPGs. Integrates LLMs, RAG, and multi-modal audio into Foundry VTT.

## Tech Stack
- Backend: Java 21, Spring Boot 3.5, Spring AI 1.1, Gradle, Lombok, PostgreSQL, OpenSearch
- Frontend: TypeScript (strict), Foundry VTT v12 module, ES2020
- Infra: Docker Compose (PostgreSQL, OpenSearch, Whisper STT, Piper TTS)

## Project Structure
- `master-server/` - Spring Boot backend (services, controllers, config, prompts, DTOs, entities)
- `master-foundry/` - Foundry VTT TypeScript module (UI, services, schemas, blueprints)

## Conventions
- Use Lombok annotations (@Data, @Builder, @Getter, @Setter) for Java classes
- Controllers are @RestController under /api/*
- Services use Spring AI ChatClient and Advisor APIs for LLM interactions
- Use record types for immutable DTOs
- Prompt templates in src/main/resources/prompts/*.txt use {placeholder} syntax
- TypeScript uses strict mode with noImplicitAny and strictNullChecks
- Foundry VTT ambient types are in src/types/foundry-ambient.d.ts
- Default narration language is Catalan; prompts adapt to configured language
- All structured LLM responses must use JSON format with explicit schemas in prompts
- Configuration in application.yml under semantic prefixes (game-master.*, whisper.*, piper-tts.*, tts.*)
- AI model routing: per-operation config with preferred/fallback models, temperature, and latency budgets
- Never hardcode API keys; use environment variables (OPENAI_API_KEY, GOOGLE_GENAI_API_KEY)

## Key Concepts
- Blueprint: JSON schema defining system-specific actor/item structures
- Director Stateful: Main narrative engine managing adventure flow and state
- Tension Level: Numeric 0-10 tracking narrative pressure
- Intent Classifier: Determines player goal (action, dialogue, meta)
- RAG Advisor: Injects game rules from OpenSearch into LLM context
- Model Routing: Per-operation AI model selection with preferred/fallback
- Wyoming Protocol: TCP protocol for local TTS/STT services

## Build Commands
- Backend: cd master-server && ./gradlew bootRun (auto-starts Docker services)
- Backend test: cd master-server && ./gradlew test
- Frontend: cd master-foundry && npm run build
- Frontend watch: cd master-foundry && npm run watch
